General.Policies.Verbs.bpnGroupOperandLe: Limit the data offer to specific Catena-X participants via Groups of Business Partner Numbers (BPN). This is more secure than the legacy Business Partner Number policy, as consumers can only see the name of your BPN groups, e.g. 'mySppliers'. BPN Groups must have been created via the Management API beforehand. Support for managing BPN Groups via the UI is coming soon.
General.Policies.Verbs.bpnOperandLeftDes: Limit the data offer to specific Catena-X participants via Business Partner Number (BPN). This is deprecated because usage policies are transparently visible by consumers. Please use BPN Groups instead.

General.Policies.Verbs.inForceDateOperan: Binds the data offer to a contract duration. This can be either achieved with two dates or a relative duration after contract agreement in which the offer can be used.
